---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Setup checklist — Mother's Gold Spice as a Sole Proprietorship" description="End-to-end registration checklist for launching Mother's Gold Spice as a Sole Proprietorship in Ricky's name — every form, fee, document, and timeline.">
  <main class="bg-cream min-h-screen">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-spice-500 font-medium mb-4">Setup checklist · Bangalore · Sole Prop</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink mb-5 leading-tight">Registering<br/>Mother's Gold Spice</h1>
        <p class="text-ink/70 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Every form, every fee, every document — sequenced for a Bangalore-based full-time IT employee running this as a side business under his own name. Account for limited evening + weekend time (Variolearn / Illustraflow is the parallel side project). End-to-end: ~3 weeks, ~₹6,000 in fees.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-sm">
          <a href="/plan" class="text-spice underline hover:text-spice-700">← Back to the launch plan</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- SUMMARY TABLE -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">At-a-glance summary</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Every registration in the order it needs to happen. Bottom row = totals.</p>

      <div class="su-table-wrap">
        <table class="su-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>#</th><th>Registration</th><th>Mandatory?</th><th>Time</th><th>Fee</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td><strong>Udyam (MSME)</strong></td><td>Yes — unlocks discounts elsewhere</td><td>30 min online</td><td>₹0</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td><strong>Shops & Establishments</strong> (Karnataka e-Karmika)</td><td>Yes — Karnataka law</td><td>2–3 days online</td><td>₹250–1,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td><strong>Business current account</strong> (HDFC / ICICI / Axis)</td><td>Yes</td><td>3–7 days</td><td>₹0–2,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td><strong>GST registration</strong></td><td>Yes if selling on Amazon; optional otherwise until ₹40L turnover</td><td>3–7 days online</td><td>₹0</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td><strong>FSSAI Basic Registration</strong></td><td>Yes — required to sell any food legally</td><td>3–7 days online</td><td>₹100/year (or ₹500 for 5 years)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td><strong>Trademark (TM-A)</strong></td><td>Optional but strongly recommended</td><td>1 evening to file; 12–24 months to certificate</td><td>₹4,500 (MSME rate)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>7</td><td><strong>Shiprocket account</strong></td><td>Yes — once shipping starts</td><td>1–2 days KYC</td><td>₹0 signup + per shipment</td></tr>
            <tr class="su-table-total"><td colspan="4"><strong>Total one-time spend</strong></td><td><strong>~₹5,500–7,500</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="su-callout">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Working assumptions for this checklist</p>
        <ul class="su-bullets">
          <li><strong>Owner:</strong> Ricky, as Sole Proprietor in his own name</li>
          <li><strong>Premises address on all registrations:</strong> Ricky's rented Bangalore flat</li>
          <li><strong>Manufacturing kitchen:</strong> Mom's home kitchen (declared address can match where production actually happens — for Basic Reg this is acceptable)</li>
          <li><strong>Channel at launch:</strong> D2C only (mothersgoldspice.com + Instagram + WhatsApp) via Shiprocket</li>
          <li><strong>Time budget:</strong> Evenings + weekends; ~3 weeks total to be fully registered</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DOCUMENTS YOU NEED -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">Documents you'll need (gather these first)</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Same documents appear repeatedly across registrations. Get a single folder ready and the rest is just form-filling.</p>

      <div class="su-doc-grid">
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">PAN card</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Your personal PAN. Used as identity proof + business identity in Sole Prop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Aadhaar card</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Mandatory for OTP verification on every government portal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Passport-size photo</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">JPG, ~50–200 KB. White background. Used on Shops & Est, FSSAI, Trademark.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Rental agreement</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">In your name (or jointly). Registered with stamp duty preferred.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Electricity bill</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Latest 1–2 months for the flat. Backup address proof.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Landlord NOC</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">One-page letter from landlord saying no objection to "small-scale food prep and packaging." Keep on file even if not asked.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Email + mobile number</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Dedicated business email if possible (e.g., ricky@mothersgoldspice.com via Cloudflare email routing — free).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Trademark image</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">High-res PNG/JPG of the combined wordmark + leaf + tagline. You already have this from the label design.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="su-doc-card">
          <p class="su-doc-name">Bank cancelled cheque</p>
          <p class="su-doc-detail">Only after the current account opens — needed for GST + Shiprocket.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 1: UDYAM -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Udyam (MSME) Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Free, 30 minutes online. Do this first because it unlocks the ₹4,500 MSME rate on Trademark (vs ₹9,000 standard).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://udyamregistration.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">udyamregistration.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>~30 minutes</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>Aadhaar (linked to mobile for OTP)</li>
        <li>PAN</li>
        <li>Email + mobile</li>
        <li>Business name: "Mother's Gold Spice"</li>
        <li>Self-declare turnover (₹0 currently → "Micro" category)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to <a href="https://udyamregistration.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">udyamregistration.gov.in</a></li>
        <li>Click "For New Entrepreneurs who are not yet registered as MSME"</li>
        <li>Enter Aadhaar → verify via OTP</li>
        <li>Fill PAN → verify</li>
        <li>Fill business details: name, type (Proprietorship), address (your flat), date of commencement, bank account (you can use personal account temporarily, update to business account later)</li>
        <li>Self-declare investment + turnover (Micro = up to ₹1 cr investment, up to ₹5 cr turnover)</li>
        <li>Submit → Udyam Registration Number (URN) issued immediately, PDF downloadable</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>Udyam Registration Certificate</strong>. Use this PDF on Trademark application + future tender bids + bank loans.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 2: SHOPS & ESTABLISHMENTS -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Shops & Establishments Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Karnataka state law. Required for any commercial activity. Bank will ask for this when opening current account.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://serviceonline.gov.in/karnataka" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">Karnataka e-Karmika</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹250–1,000 (varies by employee count; ₹0 employees for now)</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>2–3 days</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Photo of the establishment (a photo of your flat door / flat exterior works)</li>
        <li>Rental agreement + electricity bill (address proof)</li>
        <li>Business name + nature of business (food manufacturing + retail)</li>
        <li>Number of employees (0 currently — just yourself as proprietor)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to Karnataka e-Karmika portal (search "Karnataka Shops and Establishments online")</li>
        <li>Register as new applicant → verify mobile + email</li>
        <li>Fill Form A: business name, address, type, employees, nature of business</li>
        <li>Upload PAN, Aadhaar, photo, rental agreement</li>
        <li>Pay fee online (₹250 for 0 employees)</li>
        <li>Application submitted → certificate emailed in 2–3 days</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>Registration of Establishment Certificate</strong>. Renewed every 5 years.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 3: BANK ACCOUNT -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Business Current Account</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">All revenue + expenses flow through this. Required for GST, Razorpay, Shiprocket.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Bank</span>HDFC / ICICI / Axis (online-friendly) or Kotak 811 Biz</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0–2,000 opening; ₹0–500/month maintenance</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN (personal) + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Shops & Establishments certificate (from step 2)</li>
        <li>Udyam certificate (from step 1)</li>
        <li>Address proof (rental agreement + electricity bill)</li>
        <li>Passport photo</li>
        <li>Initial deposit (₹5k–25k depending on bank)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Recommended banks for a one-person Sole Prop</h3>
      <div class="su-table-wrap">
        <table class="su-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Bank</th><th>Account type</th><th>Min balance</th><th>Why pick</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Kotak Neo Biz</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹0</td><td>Fully digital onboarding, zero MAB, best for solo proprietors</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>HDFC SmartUp</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹10,000</td><td>Best Razorpay integration, founder-friendly</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>ICICI iStartup 2.0</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹10,000</td><td>Bundled with GST registration + accounting tools</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Axis Liberty for Business</strong></td><td>Current</td><td>₹0–10,000</td><td>Free first 6 months, decent app</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="su-callout">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Pro tip — avoid the visibility issue</p>
        <p>For full-time-employed founders running side businesses, the bank account in your name doesn't trigger employer alerts (banks don't share account data with employers). But the GST registration (next step) IS publicly searchable. If your IT employer has a strict anti-moonlighting policy, this is worth knowing.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 4: GST -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">4</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">GST Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Mandatory for Amazon. Optional for pure D2C/Instagram until ₹40 lakh turnover, but get it now so all channels are open.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">gst.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN + Aadhaar (mobile-linked for OTP)</li>
        <li>Photo</li>
        <li>Business address proof: rental agreement + electricity bill + landlord NOC</li>
        <li>Bank account details: name, account number, IFSC, branch (cancelled cheque)</li>
        <li>HSN codes: <strong>2001</strong> (pickled vegetables) or <strong>2008</strong> (preserved fruits) — pick the one matching your recipe</li>
        <li>Business name: same as Sole Prop name</li>
        <li>Constitution: "Proprietorship"</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to <a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">gst.gov.in</a> → "New Registration"</li>
        <li>Fill PART A: PAN, email, mobile → verify via OTP → receive TRN (Temporary Reference Number)</li>
        <li>Continue with TRN → fill PART B: business details, address, bank, HSN codes</li>
        <li>Aadhaar e-KYC verification (recommended path — avoids physical verification)</li>
        <li>Submit application</li>
        <li>If Aadhaar-verified: GSTIN issued in 3 working days. If not: officer may visit your premises within 21 days</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>15-digit GSTIN</strong>. Print this on every invoice. Print on the jar label below FSSAI number (optional but cleaner).</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 5: FSSAI BASIC -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">5</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">FSSAI Basic Registration</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">The ₹100/year tier. No kitchen inspection. Legally unlocks selling pickle via D2C from week 2 onwards.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://foscos.fssai.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">foscos.fssai.gov.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹100/year (₹500 for 5 years)</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>3–7 days</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Photo (passport size)</li>
        <li>Address proof of the premises: rental agreement OR electricity bill</li>
        <li>Food category: <strong>04.2.2.5 — Pickles, Chutneys, Sauces</strong></li>
        <li>Annual production estimate (declare a conservative number: ~5,000 jars/year for pilot)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Go to <a href="https://foscos.fssai.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">foscos.fssai.gov.in</a> → "Apply for License/Registration"</li>
        <li>Select state (Karnataka), then "Petty Food Manufacturer"</li>
        <li>Fill Form A: business name, address (your flat), nature of food business, food category, annual turnover (declare under ₹12 lakh)</li>
        <li>Upload PAN, Aadhaar, photo, address proof</li>
        <li>Pay ₹100 (1 year) or ₹500 (5 years — recommended, saves renewal hassle)</li>
        <li>Application submitted → certificate issued in 3–7 days</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>14-digit FSSAI Basic Registration Number</strong>. Prefix: <code>1XXXXXXXXX...</code>. Print on every label. Replaces the placeholder in <code>LABEL.md</code>.</div>

      <div class="su-callout-amber">
        <p class="su-callout-label">Important — the premises declaration</p>
        <p>The address on your FSSAI license is the legal manufacturing premises. Two valid options:</p>
        <ul class="su-bullets" style="margin-top: 6px;">
          <li><strong>Your rental flat</strong> — declare here, but cook in your kitchen (you'll handle production yourself on weekends)</li>
          <li><strong>Mom's home address</strong> — declare here if she's the primary cook; you'd need her name on the application as a co-proprietor or use her flat as a "branch" location</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 8px;">For solo Sole Prop in your name, declaring <strong>your flat</strong> is cleaner — you become the legal manufacturer, mom cooks "as family helper" but production technically happens at your address. Match the address to where you batch on weekends.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 6: TRADEMARK -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">6</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Trademark Registration (TM-A)</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Protect the brand before it grows. ₹4,500 at MSME rate. See <a href="/trademark" class="su-link">full trademark page</a> for deeper detail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹4,500 per class (MSME rate, with Udyam certificate)</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>1 evening to file; 12–24 months to certificate</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN + Aadhaar</li>
        <li>Passport-size photo</li>
        <li>Address proof (Aadhaar or utility bill)</li>
        <li><strong>Udyam certificate</strong> (from step 1) — this is what gets you the ₹4,500 MSME rate</li>
        <li>Trademark image: combined wordmark + leaf + tagline as a single high-res PNG (you have this from the label design)</li>
        <li>Class: <strong>29</strong> (preserved foods, pickles, chutneys)</li>
        <li>Description: "Pickles, chutneys, preserved fruits and vegetables, mango pickle, mixed pickle, condiments included in class 29"</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>First: search if "Mother's Gold Spice" is available — <a href="https://ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch/tmrsearch.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch</a> → Class 29</li>
        <li>Create applicant account on <a href="https://ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister</a></li>
        <li>Select "Individual / MSME" applicant type → upload Udyam certificate</li>
        <li>File Form TM-A: applicant name, address, mark image, class 29, description</li>
        <li>Pay ₹4,500 via netbanking/UPI</li>
        <li>Application number received same day → start using <strong>™</strong> on all labels + Instagram + website</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="su-outcome">Outcome: <strong>Trademark application number</strong> immediately; <strong>Certificate of Registration</strong> in 12–24 months. Switch from ™ to ® after the certificate.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 7: SHIPROCKET -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="su-step-header">
        <span class="su-step-num">7</span>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-1">Shiprocket Account</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">Pan-India shipping aggregator. They handle pickup-from-your-door → delivery. See <a href="/shipping" class="su-link">shipping economics page</a> for full operations detail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="su-meta">
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Portal</span><a href="https://www.shiprocket.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">shiprocket.in</a></div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Fee</span>₹0 signup, pay per shipment</div>
        <div><span class="su-meta-label">Time</span>1–2 days KYC</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">What you need</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li>PAN (personal Sole Prop)</li>
        <li>GST certificate (from step 4)</li>
        <li>Bank account details (cancelled cheque from step 3)</li>
        <li>Business address (your flat)</li>
        <li>Phone + email</li>
        <li>Pickup address (same as business address — Shiprocket courier picks up here)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Steps</h3>
      <ol class="su-step-list">
        <li>Sign up at <a href="https://www.shiprocket.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="su-link">shiprocket.in</a> as a new seller</li>
        <li>Complete KYC: upload PAN, GST cert, cancelled cheque, address proof</li>
        <li>Add pickup address (your flat)</li>
        <li>Configure couriers: select preferred (Delhivery Surface + Air; DTDC; India Post)</li>
        <li>Add bank account for COD remittance (auto-credit weekly)</li>
        <li>Integration: install Razorpay → Shiprocket auto-fetches orders, OR add orders manually from your dashboard</li>
        <li>Set up Pickup Schedule — daily / Tue+Sat / etc.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-6 mb-3">Time-saving config (critical for Variolearn-busy schedule)</h3>
      <ul class="su-bullets">
        <li><strong>Pickup schedule:</strong> Wed evening + Sat morning only (batch processing — covers the whole week)</li>
